MinItemParser* mip_create ( TSChar *  section,
int  start_pos,
int  length 
)

Creates MIN Item Parser data structures with given string data.

Parameters:
section Pointer to section string.
start_pos Start position with integer value in given section string.
length Length integer value of given section string.
Returns:
Pointer to created MIN Item Parser data structure. If error result then pointer has got INITPTR value.
Possible errors:
  • ENOMEM not enough memory to create data structure.

Frees allocated memory of MIN Item Parser data structure.

Parameters:
mip Pointer to existing MIN Item Parser data structure.

Gets first character according to given tag string from MIN Item Parser section string.

Parameters:

Returns:

Possible errors:

  • EINVAL and error code -2 if parsing operation failed.

int mip_parse_start_and_end_pos ( MinItemParser *  mip,
TSChar *  start_tag,
TSChar **  ref_start_pos,
TSChar **  ref_end_pos,
int *  ref_length,
TSChar **  ref_extra_end_pos 
)

Parses MIN Item Parser section for start, end and extra end positions including length value of parsed part of section.

Parameters:
mip Pointer to existing MIN Item Parser data structure.
start_tag Pointer to Start Tag string which be used with parsing.
ref_start_pos Start Position (char*) of parsed result string.
ref_end_pos End Position (char*) of parsed result string.
ref_length Length value of parsed result string.
ref_extra_end_pos Extra End Position (char*) of parsed result string. Used when be found quated strings.
Returns:
Returns result value. If parsing completed successfully then value 0, else returns error code.
Possible errors:
  • EINVAL and error code -1 when parsing operation failed.
